# UI and UX polish

## Structure

- Use shared shells/layouts already in the app (learner AppShell, admin shell); avoid one-off full-page heroes inside authenticated dashboards.
- Clear hierarchy: one primary action per view; secondary actions grouped and de-emphasized.

## Copy and i18n

- All visible strings through i18n; support at least Vietnamese and Japanese where the product does today.
- Product language for auth/session (no exposing raw provider jargon to learners).

## Visual discipline

- Reuse design tokens, cards, tables, and spacing rhythm from existing screens; avoid one-off palette or shadow soup.
- Calm, readable typography; respect reduced motion if adding animation.

## Accessibility and trust

- Semantic HTML, focus order, visible focus, sufficient contrast (especially primary buttons).
- Paywalls and ads must be distinguishable from learning controls; no dark patterns.

